REQUIRED EQUIPMENT
------------------


COMPUTER

 This simulation requires a Commodore Amiga with at least 1 Mb of RAM.

CONTROLS

 The simulation can be run with a mouse, keyboard and joystick.

DISPLAY

 This simulation requires a colour display.

DISK DRIVES

 The Ancient Art of War in the Skies can be played from 3.5"
floppy disks. However, it works best if installed onto a hard disk

IMPORTANT

 The Ancient Art of War in the Skies should not be played from the
disks enclosed. You must either copy the original disks onto backup
floppy disks (see Making Backup Disks), or use the Install program to
create a subdirectory on your hard disk.

 If you attempt to play from the disks enclosed they may become
permanently altered.


INSTALLATION
------------

INSTALLATION CONCEPTS

 The Ancient Art of War in the Skies is not copy protected. This
means you can copy the game files from the original disks however
you prefer - to other floppy disks, or to a hard disk These files are
normal in all respects and should not cause special problems when
backing up, restoring, or optimizing a hard disk. However, keep the
original disks handy.

 The Ancient Art of War in the Skies has been left unprotected for
your conyenience in making backup copies and when playlng from a
hard drive. However, making additional copies to give away or sell is a
Copyright Violation. See the Copyright Notice at the end of this
document.

MAKING BACKUP DISCS

To make backup discs follow the procedure below.

1 Write protect your original game disks. Flip the tab and make
  sure you can see the hole in the top corner of each disk
2 Load WorkBench
3 Locate an icon called Shell
4 Double click on this icon to open an AmigaShell window
5 Place your original disc in the internal drive
6 Type DISKCOPY DFO: TO DFO: press [Return]
7 Follow the on screen instructions and repeat steps 4 and 5 for
  all the discs

INSTALLING ON HARD DISK

Boot up your hard disk as normal and insert The Ancient Art of
War in the Skies Game disk. Open this disk and double click on the
HD INSTALL, icon. Please follow any on-screen prompts. A drawer
labelled SKIES , will be created on your hard disk, containing all
necessary files.


RUNNING - THE ANCIENT ART OF WAR IN THE SKIES
---------------------------------------------

FLOPPY DISK

 If your computer has KickStart in ROM, turn off your computer
and insert your backup Game disk switch on your computer and
double click on SKlES and the program will auto-load.

 If your computer does not have KickStart in ROM, load
KickStart as normal. Insert your backup Game disk at the
Workbench prompt and double click on SKIES.

Follow any on screen prompts requesting disk changes.

HARD DISK

Boot up your hard disk as normal. Double click on the SKlES
drawer and then on the SKIES game icon.

SAVED GAMES
You may save games currently under way and recontinue them at
a later date. Games may be saved onto your hard drive or onto the
back up floppy Game disk.

In addition, you can use the Move Campaigns, option from the
Campaign Editor to move all the campaigns to your own disk. If you
do this, make sure the Campaign Path in the Game Options is set to
the name of the disk.

LOADING A SAVED GAME

Saved games can be loaded as a pre-game option.


